    <item>
      <title>Netcat with SSH Port Forwarding</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I have encountered a problem with getting access to the private local service which available from the local machine.
And I need to write application using this service in another network.
I have only one port open to access the local machine &lt;code&gt;ssh&lt;/code&gt; daemon.
After a few minutes of problem discussion, we decided to use &lt;code&gt;NetCat&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table class=&quot;highlighttable&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&quot;linenos&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;linenodiv&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;1
2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&quot;code&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;mkfifo pipe
&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt; 1 &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;do &lt;/span&gt;nc -l -p 8080 &amp;lt; pipe &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; ssh gw_to_private_net -p 22977  &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;nc 192.168.12.230 80&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; tee pipe&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
